text.text: Adorable little coffeehut serving delicious Kaladi  Brothers espresso. Baristas are cheerful and friendly. Great location, especially if you are waiting at Jiffy Lube or the DMV.

I've been gone for over two years and they still have gigantic burritos for the same decent price. I recommend the works with onions, peppers, sour cream, salsa added. Well worth the $6. I also like their signature Barista Cat (WC Americano) and the high caffeine white coffee option.
They've done well with their business and are able to stand out over many other coffee huts/shops.
Best breakfast burritos in town! They are MASSIVE, delicious and filling. They also always have delicious coffee that is consistently the same great taste.
